Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.60,0:17:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's motionless.\NIt's sachetan meaning bliss. There is an
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.03,0:17:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite presence. The presence of the\Ninfinite peace of God which is the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.76,0:17:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,essence of divinity unfolding. Oh yes.\NIt says satan right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.31,0:17:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It it's an emergence. It's an affluence.\NUh it is also silent and wordless
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is all-encompassing.\NIt's transformative and one realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.64,0:17:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that is one's identity. That's who who\Nor what you are is that state which is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.60,0:17:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear\Nharmonious. It's intrinsic. It has no
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.72,0:17:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,location.\NIt's total
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.64,0:17:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's unifying.\NThere is no me as separate from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.55,0:18:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You or separateness disappears and\Nthere's just a total oneness within the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,oneness. This oneness takes on\Nlinear characteristics. It the mind then
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,differentiates as me and you and them\Netc.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.52,0:18:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So that's the first slide.\NIllumination
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.96,0:18:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is level 600. Yes. All right. So, we'll\Ngo to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.00,0:18:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh so we're talking today also about\Nself-realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.72,0:18:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nall this looks very wordy. I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.72,0:18:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm going to do about all that.\N>> But
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.60,0:18:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,no, no, no. These are fine.\Nuh self realization because that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.28,0:18:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about today. Um we're\Ntalking about mysticism. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.72,0:18:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,essentially what is mysticism?\NThe ordinary mind is thinking mind. It
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks in a linear linear definitions.\NIt has pronouns of myself and and you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nthe mystic uh state comes about in a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.08,0:19:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear. It doesn't come about uh as a\Nresult of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion has to do with a lot of\Ninformation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.36,0:19:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and mastering the information. The\Ninformation then becomes integrated and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.36,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,can become quite sophisticated.\NTheology,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.00,0:19:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced theology is very fascinating\Nsubject and you can spend a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.08,0:19:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime studying uh theology. Huh?\NIn the mystic the understanding comes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.16,0:19:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,about in a different way.\NThe under the understanding is an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.60,0:19:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,eulgence.\NIt's a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.08,0:20:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that requires no thinkingness at all.\NDoesn't require information
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which\Nensues as the mystical state doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.79,0:20:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,know anything at all about religion.\NIgnorant about religion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,may never have even heard of it. Right?\NI've spoken of the inner states that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred in this lifetime\Nbecause they exhibit pretty much a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.48,0:20:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the basic concepts that we want to\Ncover today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.24,0:20:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,intention uh sets up I think intention\Nand commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,probably in a number of lifetimes sets\Nup the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.55,0:20:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for the mystical events see\Nso the first mystical event which I've
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:21:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,related before\Nwas to come out of nothingness at age
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,three at age three out of the void\Nnothingness non-awareness non
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence.\NThere was suddenly a shock, a very
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.03,0:21:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,stunning shock of suddenly the awareness\Nof existence from non-existence to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,existence\Nwas a stunning shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.36,0:21:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like being in a dark cave and\Nsuddenly all the cleague lights are
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.28,0:21:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,turned on. It was like that stunning\Nstunningness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.88,0:21:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not pleased.\NNot only did I exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.12,0:21:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but a body went with it. And I think\NI've related that before. It was bad
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.40,0:21:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,enough to exist. And then I looked down\Nand here is this little body in a wagon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.64,0:22:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,stuck out there by its mother to sit in\Nthe sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.12,0:22:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It took uh many years to recover from\Nthe shock. of of discovering uh
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.60,0:22:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,existence. It took some 36 years in fact\Nand was the infinite reality existence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.12,0:22:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,versus non-existence.\NAnd this is one of the coins one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.24,0:22:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,dilemmas that you pass uh in Zen pathway\Nis reality is existence or a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.84,0:22:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence.\NSo as I've said before, it took 36 years
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.44,0:22:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Zen teachings uh are that any\Nsuch a statement in itself is facious
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.24,0:22:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,any that would be a judgment and a\Nconcept conceptual thinking. So existing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is a is a concept with no existence and\Nnon-existence is a concept with no
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:22:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NSo when you let go of all such con
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.60,0:23:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,contextual statements uh you don't have\Na problem with existence versus
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.15,0:23:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence\Nbecause there is no duality neither one
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.32,0:23:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of them having reality.\NSo one way to get rid of problems is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.67,0:23:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,just disappear their reality and now\Nyou're free of them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.64,0:23:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're free and liberated forever.\NOh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.67,0:23:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.72,0:23:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that awareness which is a quite profound\Nawareness it really is not resolved till
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.08,0:23:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 850. So that's a\Npretty advanced dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.76,0:23:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say it took some 30 years to\Nresolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.24,0:23:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The next major event was in this level\Nin this consciousness here was um
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.03,0:24:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,um the the the experience I spoken about\Nin the snowbank
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that uh as a child I was quite religious\Netc. But the religion had nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.40,0:24:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with these phenomena.\NThey had nothing at all to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.24,0:24:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nyou can memorize all the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.00,0:24:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,literature in the world and when the\Nmystical experience occurs it has
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.40,0:24:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing at all to do with everything you\Nspent your whole lifetime studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.48,0:24:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not connected. they're not in\Nthe same realm. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.40,0:24:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I think as I've related before, I'm\Nrepeating it this morning because it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.64,0:24:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,fits into the whole subject of the\Nmystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.00,0:24:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, one time in a blizzard I in northern\NWisconsin I had a paper route and uh, it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.88,0:24:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was cold and windy, terribly windy and\Nterribly cold and uh, huge snow banks on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.48,0:24:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,each side of the highway and the snow\Nbanks had been there some while and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.32,0:24:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there was like a crust in the snow but\Nthe snow was quite you know 8 10 feet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:25:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,high. So to get out of the wind, I knock\NI crushed my way into the snowbank and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.88,0:25:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly dug out a little cave and and\Nand snuck inside the cave. There's no
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.72,0:25:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,such word as snuck, but I did it anyway.\NSneaked
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.12,0:25:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,snuck into the Anyway, I wanted to get\Nout of the wind. I was still in good
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.72,0:25:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,shape. I have plenty of physical energy.\NIt wasn't near death or anything like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.32,0:25:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that. On the contrary, I was quite\Nvigorous and but I wanted to get out of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.36,0:25:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the wind. Just a little uh\Nlittle smell of relief in the wind. So I
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.27,0:25:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,climbed inside of this uh little cave\Nand uh and tried to relax and and then
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.60,0:25:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nowhere\Nout of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.20,0:25:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,came uh\NA profound infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.40,0:26:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,radiance of love\Nbeyond all imagination, beyond human
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.00,0:26:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,love,\Ntimeless, timeless and eternal. No
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.64,0:26:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning and no end.\NCloser than your own self,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.96,0:26:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,closer to your reality, to what you\Nthink of yourself than your personal
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.88,0:26:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,identity as yourself.\NAnd I realized this is the core of who I
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.55,0:26:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,am. It was eternal\Nforeverness. Foreverness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.40,0:26:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that that which you are\Nis eternal. Infinite love
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.24,0:26:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,without thought, without realization,\Nwith no pronouns.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.52,0:26:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of that which you are\Nis not different is infinite with no
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.08,0:26:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning and no end.\NAnd it is not different than infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.52,0:27:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely perfect love.\NThat's the revelation of the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.55,0:27:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your own existence. Let's see if that\Napplies to everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.40,0:27:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth of everyone's existence\Nhere. Resist. That's the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.36,0:27:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone's existence here. D\Nthat which you are infinite love existed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.44,0:27:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,forever\Nwith no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.27,0:27:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So all that's left is to realize that.\NLet it snap.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.24,0:27:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Go get a snowbank someplace and dig a\Nhole in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.48,0:27:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,today's world that would make it the\Nholy snowbank and then put a thing over
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.15,0:27:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it and guard rail around it.\NThere are places like that, chairs where
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.00,0:28:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody sat and now they become revered\Nholy chairs, you know. This is where so
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.96,0:28:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and so sat, you know.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.72,0:28:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,reality being on it is the snowbank\Neventually melted, of course, so it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.08,0:28:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't put a holy placard there in\Nfront of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.48,0:28:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness. So\Nthat was uh
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.60,0:28:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,very profound uh beyond all learning\Nhaving nothing to do with church or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.67,0:28:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,theology. Uh religion was uh somehow\Nseparate from it. There are two
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.64,0:28:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,different boxes. Two different boxes.\NReligion was something else. And u
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.72,0:28:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,although I was very religious young that\Nreligiosity had nothing to do with that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.96,0:28:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. They're two different\Nrealms. They're not connected. There is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.96,0:28:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,no connection between that the linear\Nand the nonlinear. They are two
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.48,0:28:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,different realms.\NThe surrendering to the presence then uh
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.79,0:29:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,within of the essence and the core and\Nthe source of your reality is a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,subtlety.\NNow the mis the knowledge of the mystic
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.24,0:29:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,arises\Num the studying and all that only sets
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.03,0:29:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,up a stage\Nbut it's self-revealing. So mysticism
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.12,0:29:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is surrendering to the self\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.72,0:29:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the capacity of of divinity within to\Nreveal itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.08,0:29:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And it reveals itself when it is\Nkarmically propitious to do so. Not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.64,0:29:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,necessarily when you want it to happen.\NIt can happen at very inconvenient
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.67,0:29:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,times. You find yourself completely\Nincapacitated
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.36,0:29:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting there in a state of bliss on a\Nrock and you can't get up and move or
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.79,0:29:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,leave or anything.\NIt happened to me in Sedona and sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.03,0:30:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on a rock, the state of bliss was so\Nprofound. There was no capacity to get
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.00,0:30:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,off the rock and it seemed like\Nthat would be the end of the trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.84,0:30:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the they they cart you\Naway, I guess. So it came across my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.52,0:30:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that they cart you away. I said well so\Nthey cart you away then they put you in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.52,0:30:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a hospital. Well then they put you in a\Nhospital
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.00,0:30:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what prevailed the state of uh\Nsacha and nanda nothing interferes with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.48,0:30:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NNow there was no preceding states. You
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.24,0:30:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,see you know\Nwho was the Indian guru that fell down
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.03,0:30:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thought he had died and woke up in a\Ndifferent state. Ramana Mahari. Yes. So
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.88,0:30:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the mysticala mystic occasion\Nout of nowhere at all he fell down fell
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.64,0:30:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,felt he had died and woke up in a\Ncompletely different state.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.15,0:30:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he hadn't been discovered by\Nothers, he probably would have just
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.44,0:31:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,starved to death there. Eaten by bugs\Nand dehydration. And because in that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.60,0:31:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,state there is no need for anything.\NNo need for anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.32,0:31:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Food, water, no need for anything. It's\Na state of uh absolute completeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.39,0:31:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It can last for considerable lengths of\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.32,0:31:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the the profound state eventually at\Nleast in this case one learns how to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.64,0:31:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,deal with it.\NThe state continues. The state
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.72,0:31:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,continues.\NIt sometimes gets stronger and sometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.79,0:31:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,weaker\Nand eventually leads to depending on
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.76,0:31:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one's karmic propensities\Nuh the capacity to continue to be in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.08,0:31:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,world\Nand function in some kind of capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.67,0:32:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about which you yourself as a person\Nhave nothing to say. It's as though the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.91,0:32:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,world says do this and therefore the\Nresponse is so you do this, you do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.44,0:32:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If the world said do this, you would do\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.12,0:32:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The world says uh there's no doctor\Nhere. Uh you world needs you to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.24,0:32:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and practice for a while. So you do that\Nthen they don't need you as a doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.79,0:32:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore. So you quit that.\NIt doesn't make any difference. One is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.96,0:32:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just doing what is autonomous actually\Nbecause there is no person doing it. The
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.72,0:32:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,doing this and the happeningness\Nis self-emergent and self-fulfilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.91,0:32:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the role the role of being an an\Nactive physician is just a role. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.55,0:32:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not who you are. You know when you get\Nto heaven St. computer doesn't check you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.91,0:33:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in under doctors here, dentists there's\Nhousekeepers there. It's totally
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.03,0:33:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant to your inner reality. It's\Nthe doing this. So you also do carpentry
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.48,0:33:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do all kinds of things you know\Nuh because those are capa capacities of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.64,0:33:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that uh of the degree of linear domain\Nwhich you learn to operate. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.20,0:33:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear then is operating in a linear\Ndomain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.12,0:33:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the mystic there is an automatic\Nadjustment about it. You don't think
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.32,0:33:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about how I will be with that in as much\Nas I'm not that. Uh the being that way
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.08,0:33:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,happens of its ownness just as the\Nlecturing happens of its own known
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.24,0:33:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,ownness.\NUh and although you can put put together
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.08,0:33:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,some slides there's no knowing what's\Ngoing to be said at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.91,0:33:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nself-realization. Yes. Well, the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.72,0:34:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried. Oh yeah, I see. We tried to\Ngive it some form. Uh the levels 700 and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.24,0:34:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,up. So Raman Mahari and Mr. Gadada\NMaharaj.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.64,0:34:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Um if these represent the sage uh the\Nrealization may take you out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.24,0:34:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,world or you may remain within the world\Nand then the the label you're labeled
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.87,0:34:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the sage. Your sage is one who is\Nrealized a mystic who has realized but
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.39,0:34:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,stays in the world to serve a teaching\Nfunction or a communication function.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.39,0:34:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh in this what what happens is the\Npersonal sense of self
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.11,0:34:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,uh unceremoniously\Nis dissolved into the major self.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.39,0:34:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no warning about it. It just\Ncomes on and it's beatotific. It really
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.83,0:34:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is. uh uh timeless.\NWhat happens is you stop identifying
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.63,0:35:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with linear definition and instead you\Nrealize that you are one with essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.40,0:35:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One sees the world as a oneness. Within\Nthe oneness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.00,0:35:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there is definitions definitions\Ninteracting but they are not separate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.24,0:35:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,selves. They are not separate from the\Nall. They're like a condensation. It
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.52,0:35:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would be like the sky darkens and the\Nfog darkens and then raindrops fall out
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.44,0:35:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of it, but it's still all the same sky\Nand the same weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.35,0:35:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nso the world is witnessed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.68,0:35:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,allincclusive.\NThe context then is the wholeness and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.64,0:35:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness of divinity.\NAnd you see the perfection of all that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.40,0:35:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.20,0:35:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfection of all that occurs. How\Ncan you see perfection
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.80,0:36:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world that it seems to be\Nimperfect?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.96,0:36:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because what you see as imperfect\Nis the perfection of that particular
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.59,0:36:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,program.\NBeat up old blind crippled laying on the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.28,0:36:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,floor is the perfection of being old\Nand laying on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.88,0:36:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand that? Yeah.\NOne becomes the perfection. One is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.35,0:36:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,always the perfection. Divinity\Nwithin is called God imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.07,0:36:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The state is comes about as a\Nconsequence of what the world calls
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.68,0:36:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,grace. The world has no linear logical\Nexplanation of why these states should
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.00,0:36:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,occur.\NWe know however from our own studies
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.28,0:37:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that committing your life to God through\Nprayer, devotion etc. precipitates these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.11,0:37:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,states eventuating sooner or later.\NThey can be subtle, they can be
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.68,0:37:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,profound, they can take you right out of\Nthe world altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.48,0:37:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nanyway, one sets up a karmic propensity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.28,0:37:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then the the response is called grace\Nbecause it's non-causal and nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.96,0:37:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NCreation then appears to you as an
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.88,0:37:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,unfoldment.\NIt's hard to describe the room. This
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.92,0:37:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,room\Nis one complete unity in which that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.35,0:37:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which looks like separate individuals\Nis perceptual only and not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.92,0:38:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all one complete total united unity\Nwithin which there's definitions as
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.56,0:38:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,various bodies and all but those are the\Nexpressions of the unity. The
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.04,0:38:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions of the unity the expressions\Nof the you of the rain are look like
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.24,0:38:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,separate raindrops. Uhhuh.\NHowever, the rain is one. So there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.32,0:38:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,separation.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.35,0:38:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we've said before that evolution and\Ncreation are one and the same thing. So
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.72,0:38:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the one thing we've emphasized in almost\Nevery lecture is to realize that nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.96,0:38:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is causing anything. So one jump from\Nbeing logical and sensible and sane that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.40,0:38:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,being very bizarre a mystic\Nis to let go that anything is causing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.40,0:38:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.\NNothing is causing anything anywhere in
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.76,0:38:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.\NWow. Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.72,0:39:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds mad to me.\NThat is true. Is this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.56,0:39:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that is true on the level of essence.\NIt's not true on the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.83,0:39:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,perception. On the level of perception,\Nthere always seems to be a this causing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.35,0:39:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a that. There's always a victim and a\Nperpetrator. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.76,0:39:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would politics be without a victim\Nand a perpetrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.07,0:39:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always an evil one causing harm\Nto the innocent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.59,0:39:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there's always causation. Now,\Nemergence has which we've been lecturing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.72,0:39:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about for years and written about is now\Nbecoming a doctrine in pretty much
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.32,0:39:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced scientific theory. Emergence is\Nnow becoming described
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.72,0:39:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh as a scientific uh statement\Nemergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.80,0:40:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution is creation. So there's no\Nconflict between evolution and creation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.59,0:40:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because evolution is creation and\Ncreation expresses itself as evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.96,0:40:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nthe infinite field out of which all
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.44,0:40:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena and existence arise is the\Nfield of consciousness itself. The field
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.20,0:40:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself which in other\Nter terminology is called the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.68,0:40:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,nature. The Buddha nature then is\Nnonlinear non-defined has no content
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.16,0:40:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and arises as an awareness when all\Nbarriers to it have been removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.07,0:40:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I will give you a lecture this\Nmorning,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.68,0:40:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a short lecture,\Na glorious lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.35,0:41:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a lecture of great profoundity.\NYou'll notice all Zen masters etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.56,0:41:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,always give you a flowery presentation\Nof what they're about to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.80,0:41:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You will now hear the greatest and most\Nprofound teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.59,0:41:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which has come down through 18\Npatriarchs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.00,0:41:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from mount. Yep.\NIn which the great master said the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.59,0:41:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,following.\NTo get it, you've got to really strain
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.68,0:41:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,your awareness and your will to\Nunderstand
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.88,0:41:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the wisdom that is about to be\Nproclaimed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.11,0:41:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Go.\NThat is the wisdom of the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.28,0:41:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,reality\Nwhich I have transmitted to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.92,0:42:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, never say that you were not\Nthat you did not hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.80,0:42:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Did everyone hear it?\NAh,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.68,0:42:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all these bodhis zappas here, all the\NBuddhas of the future. First you hear it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.80,0:42:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,from those who know it, and then it's\Ntransmitted silently down through the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.35,0:42:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,ages as unspoken. Because the minute you\Nspeak, it's no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.16,0:42:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth.\NSo now you know this the core of Zen
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.59,0:42:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism.\NIt only took 30 years of meditation to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.35,0:42:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,get it. You know,\Nlook at all the black widowed spiders I
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.07,0:42:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,could have carried.\NAll right. So
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.52,0:43:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the self-realization then is autonomous.\NIt comes about of its own. There is no
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.00,0:43:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,cause. We know that there is like a\Npropitious readiness in which the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.59,0:43:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,condition is more likely to occur.\NJust as it's more likely to occur, the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.00,0:43:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,rain is more likely to occur on a cloudy\Nday when the humidity is a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.88,0:43:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,level, etc. But that doesn't cause it to\Nrain because right now it's not raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.92,0:43:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it caused it to rain, it would be\Nraining right now. So there's other
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.20,0:43:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,factors involved. Uh-huh. Readiness and\Nwill and karmic propensities
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.31,0:43:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and ultimately is it is the grace of\NGod. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.96,0:43:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The grace of God\Nit's autonomous
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.76,0:43:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a state of awareness.\NIt's beyond cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.48,0:43:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is the that which is speaking now\Nis what it is. That which is is speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.48,0:44:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,now is an impersonal awareness\Nknowingness which has nothing to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.83,0:44:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the speaker.\NUh it uh speaks on its own when it's
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.92,0:44:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,propitious to do so. So if it fulfills a\Nrole of a teacher then the perushia the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.00,0:44:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,speaker the infinite self within will\Nspeak uh and its speakingness is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.64,0:44:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically correlated to the level of\Nthe listener.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.72,0:44:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, something very simple would\Nbe said uh to a child. I see. And yet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.59,0:44:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the child could get it and then on the\Nway home pray as George was telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.59,0:44:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fact that it's simple doesn't mean they\Nwon't get it beyond. So the mystical is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.96,0:44:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomous spontaneous.\NIt's a field of awareness which arises
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.56,0:45:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not as not caused by phenomena.\NSo listening here on the way to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.72,0:45:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh Andrea Bochelli.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.48,0:45:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The music of Andre Bochelli\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.83,0:45:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,causes people to cry.\NNow, it isn't the music that causes you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.24,0:45:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to cry.\NIt's the energy field that that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.04,0:45:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible beauty brings up and it's\Nthat energy field that makes you cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.68,0:45:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's no point of worshiping the\Nmusic of Andrea Bochelli because what
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.48,0:45:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you cry is not the music but the\Nenergy that arises in association with
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.40,0:45:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.04,0:45:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mystical state is more like an\Nenergy vibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.72,0:45:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a field of consciousness. A field of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.11,0:46:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So at one of his concerts,\Neveryone goes into an enchanted state.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.52,0:46:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Enchanted. It's enchanting.\NYou're in a different state.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.16,0:46:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in a different state\Nbecause the incredible beauty of the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.80,0:46:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,music transports you to a different\Nstate of consciousness. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.48,0:46:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not caused because you have to have\Nthe capacity to respond that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.28,0:46:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know from the brain physiology\Nthat people that whose brain function is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.96,0:46:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,over here will respond by crying to\Nbeauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.31,0:46:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,These people will say turn that off for\NGod's sake. I can't hear the ball game.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.92,0:46:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know\Nthat's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.76,0:46:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched people be very annoyed by\Nbeauty, demand that it be turned off.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.00,0:47:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn that turn that off. Turn that off.\NThey're listening to the most
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.83,0:47:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible, beautiful music in the whole\Nworld. And it makes you weep with this
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.72,0:47:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty and they'll say, "Turn that off.\NTurn that off."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.11,0:47:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's a different brain function.\NThose people, you know, are limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.80,0:47:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They grew up to here and then they\Nstopped there somehow. And
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.24,0:47:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they they didn't get to the heart yet.\NSo it's like the the mystic the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.44,0:47:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,energy has now risen.\NUh technically uh it's called the eye
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the third the Buddha body. So the\Naetheric body you see the energizing of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.72,0:47:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the nervous system comes about through\Nthe atheric body and it's a level 200
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.59,0:47:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and up you develop an atheric body. Now\Nbelow 200 people do not have an atheric
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.56,0:47:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,body.\NI don't know how how they get along but
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.07,0:48:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they do.\NUnder 200 they do not have an atheric
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.31,0:48:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,body.\NHow do you like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.92,0:48:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So you cannot expect people who don't\Neven have an atheric body
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.59,0:48:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to faint with joy at the sound of Andrea\NBochelli because they don't have that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.52,0:48:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which vibrates to it. There is no\Nresonance you know like a sounding board
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.83,0:48:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,tuning fork you resonate. Huh? So\Nlacking that capacity which is genetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.28,0:48:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see that the majority of mankind\Nis unable to respond to beauty, love and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.07,0:48:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,truth. Majority.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.59,0:48:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are today's hard words. They are\Ntruthful. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.11,0:48:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the unfortunate truth.\NA lot of competition for the title of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.83,0:49:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the unfortunate truth.\NThe unfortunate truth unfortunately is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.88,0:49:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,not the truth. So anyway, aside from\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.55,0:49:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh so this is a capacity\Npeople in this audience are motivated
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.28,0:49:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,differently than the rest of the world.\NYou think the rest of the world is like
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.76,0:49:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you? They are not like you. First of\Nall, he would not sit here and listen to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.80,0:49:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a lecture on the mystic\Nin the linear domain. There is no such
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.55,0:49:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,thing as the mystic and uh the skeptics\Npeople like skeptics you know uh can't
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.00,0:49:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,believe anything uh that is beyond\Npedestrian and literal materialistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.88,0:49:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So\Nthe reason uh neuroscience which
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.52,0:49:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,investigates consciousness has been a\Ntotal failure thus far is they don't
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.35,0:50:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,understand how it works.\NThe energy body is so-called atheric
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.48,0:50:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,body.\NNow if you know Maxwell Maxwell is a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.92,0:50:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,famous scientist discovered that if you\Nput a magnetic field around a wire it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.83,0:50:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,produces electricity. Wow. That's how\Nyou get generators going. And the same
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.20,0:50:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,thing happens if you put electricity\Naround the wire you get magnetism. Mag
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.20,0:50:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,magnetism electricity.\NSo the way the human nervous system and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.40,0:50:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,practically nobody in this whole world\Nknows this. Nobody even knows this is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.44,0:50:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that the atheric body which is the\Nenergy body
