Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.71,1:16:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. We feel sorry for you now. You can\Nlet go of it. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.71,1:16:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the evolution of consciousness\Nin this then an autonomous state reveals
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.64,1:16:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,itself effortlessly.\NIt may have preceding warnings that it's
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.67,1:16:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,going to come on. Eventually, it takes\Nover and may take you out of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.23,1:16:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Took me out of the world. I gave up uh\Nthe largest psychiatric practice of his
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.36,1:16:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,kind in the United States. 100 uh people\Nworking for us, 2,000 patients, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.76,1:16:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,walked away from it, came out and sat\Ncross-legged all by myself for a couple
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.36,1:16:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,years on top of the black widow spiders\Nand remembered to eat once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.92,1:16:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've told you stories about that\Nbefore. All by yourself, the body
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.64,1:16:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears and uh and you walk past the\Nmirror and suddenly you go into shock. I
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.60,1:17:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,can remember going into a shock stunned\Nthat there was somebody in the mirror
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.71,1:17:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and another time walking into the wall.\NWalk right smack into the wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.52,1:17:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to walk right through it.\NThe spirit would just walk through it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.12,1:17:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand the physical body went right against
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.28,1:17:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nbroke my nose and everything. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.15,1:17:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the choice the choice is you can\Nleave the world. You can leave the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.32,1:17:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,world. There's another alternative uh is\Nyou can stay in the world but yeah more
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.28,1:17:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or less like an ashram\Nyou don't participate in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.44,1:17:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,however\Nyou're available and people come and
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.80,1:17:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,visit you and uh you see people from all\Nover the world
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.92,1:17:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can lead the life of a\Ncontemplative
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.60,1:17:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,quiet retired from the\Npeople come to visit you and what they
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.96,1:18:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for really is to pick up that\Nenergy, pick up that energy. So
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.12,1:18:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes what you do is you return to\Nteaching so that you can be available
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.52,1:18:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for others to reach that energy because\Nnot everyone is capable of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.56,1:18:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,traveling long distance and the and the\Nexpense and the money is such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.60,1:18:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So Ramano Mahari and Nagadana Maharaj uh\Nserve that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.88,1:18:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,serve that m the mystic who then has a\Nlimited uh role serves as a teacher for
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.67,1:18:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,those who seek him as a teacher but\Ndon't necessarily go out into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.60,1:18:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it available to any large\Nnumbers of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.92,1:18:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My own uh inner capacity was always the\Nrelieving of suffering. That's why I
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.60,1:18:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,became a physician. That's why I had a\Nspecial relationship with animals
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.32,1:18:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to the relief of suffering. Whether it's\Na beagle flipping his legs upside down,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.44,1:19:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the compassion leads you to then become\Na physician or a healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.28,1:19:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have been a very good uh doctor,\Nanimal doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.80,1:19:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the observation of the totality of\Nhuman suffering is what fully motivated
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.92,1:19:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,my staying in the world. As I remember\None time I was highly religious. I
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.60,1:19:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,walked through the field uh thinking\Nabout nothing at all and suddenly the
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.32,1:19:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,totality\Nof human suffering throughout all of
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.15,1:19:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,time\Nwas like revealed. It was staggering
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.80,1:19:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,staggering beyond all description.\Nstaggering in its enormity. Yeah. And
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.71,1:19:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,its consequence.\NAnd in that instant is when I became an
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.76,1:19:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,atheist. And I told you about my years\Nas an atheist
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.48,1:19:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought it was God that had\Ncreated all this suffering. And I didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.19,1:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that all that suffering I was\Nseeing was the consequence of the human
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.76,1:20:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ego. It wasn't the creation of divinity.\NIt was the creation of the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.56,1:20:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore I finally transcended it\Nwith that realization that it was the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.12,1:20:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,human ego. But nevertheless, the desire\Nto relieve suffering in all of its
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.60,1:20:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,capacities is why I had such a large\Nclinic and tried all kinds of innovative
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.96,1:20:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,approaches, anything that would help the\Npatient. Uh not all of it conventional,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.52,1:20:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of it non-conventional and the\Nnon-conventional things were extremely
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.52,1:20:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh useful. Therefore, scientism and\Nskepticism and all are very
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.44,1:20:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,self-limiting because the clinician uses\Nthings other than academic medicine. He
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.12,1:20:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uses intuitive understanding\Nand the how much you care for the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.92,1:20:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,patient has an impact. I'm not talking\Nabout counter transference, but who you
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.56,1:20:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,are to the patient has a profound\Neffect. And I myself were cured of many
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.08,1:21:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ailments.\NUh, I remember I had a chronic
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.44,1:21:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,intractable uh, perforating ulcer that\Nwas perforating into the pancreas and
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.19,1:21:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,potentially lethal and uh, acupuncture\Nwas just brand new in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.12,1:21:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,first the first acupuncture patients I\Nwas one of the first ones in the whole
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.04,1:21:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,United States and after three treatments\Nthree treatments and I remember the
